y gets,'' said a senior executive at another rival firm.=20
The stunning near-collapse of Enron -- bankruptcy was only averted, some ana=
lysts say, by the Dynegy acquisition -- closes a chapter on one of the most =
influential careers in the history of the energy business.=20
The ugly circumstances of Enron's downfall, including the revelation that pa=
rtnerships were used to move debt off the company's balance sheet and that E=
nron overstated profits in the last five years by almost $600 million, have =
